Speaker 2: Okay. So I went ahead and canceled out that refill,

Speaker 2: So when you get this new bottle in the mail in a few days, on the bottle,

Speaker 1: it's going to say AGV, and it's also going to say Greenstone.

Speaker 2: Greenstone is the name of Pfizer's manufacturer in France.

Speaker 1: And then on the pills, the only number imprinted is going to be the number 100

Speaker 2: for the milligrams. And those are the two ways you can confirm it's AGV.

Speaker 1: Because right now, your bottle says APCO, and on your pills, it says AC390 or 340.

Speaker 2: Those are just generics. So you can just go ahead and toss those in the trash.

Speaker 1: And then I'm going to pause your refills for six months.

Speaker 2: I'm going to pause it until July 31, 2026.

Speaker 1: Because if I cancel you out now, it will cancel your profile,

Speaker 2: and the pharmacy would not be able to send you that replacement.

Speaker 1: And then I'll give you my extension, so you can call me back

Speaker 2: and let me know how the AGV works out for you.

Speaker 1: Okay. Please?

Speaker 2: Sure. It's 0020.

Speaker 2: Yeah. 0020.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Exactly.
